Conch should have produce the new smartphone because it has a positive NPV. Its IRR (27.13%) is higher than the required rate of return (12%). The profitability index is bigger than 1, hich means with every $1 investment, Conch will make an addition of $0.465 as profit. The payback period is 2.675 years which means that the new smartphone will break even after 2.675 years and for the rest duration of the new smartphone project, Conch can take all the profits. All the decision criteria show that the new smartphone will be profitable and Conch should accept this project.					


